## APPROACH
**Audit → Fix → Polish → Monetize.** Go function-by-function, page-by-page. Read every file thoroughly. Identify what's broken, incomplete, confusing, or poorly implemented. Fix it. Make the user flow intuitive. Only add Stripe/payments after the core product is solid.

When auditing, always:
- Read the FULL file (don't skim)
- Check for: dead code, hardcoded values, missing error handling, poor UX, broken flows, inconsistent patterns
- Test the logic mentally: "If a user does X, what happens?"
- Suggest and implement improvements, don't just list problems
- After fixing, verify with lints

